I have been a lurker here for sometime...   I find the subject fascinating, but my tecnnical skills are so limited I rarely feel like I can contribute anything to the group.  This post touched me so deeply, though, I felt I had to reply.

     I have lost a number of well loved animal companions over the years, from Black Labs to White Ferrets to cats of various persuasions.  (The most recent being a tawny colored short-hair named O&#39;Rafferty, who looked like a pigmy puma.)  

     While I have little experience with animal EVP&#39;s, I have no doubt that I will see them all again someday.  If they are not waiting for me on the other side, I&#39;m not going...

     Would love to see posts from anyone that has experience with animal EVP&#39;s or other proof of companion animal survival.  Do those on the other side have anything to say about this subject?

     I deeply sympathise with your loss...   Just reading your post brought tears to my eyes.

Nightshade

